Misanthrope$$a person who hates or distrusts humankind
Slovenly$$untidy especially in personal appearance
Morose$$having a sullen and gloomy disposition -- marked by or expressive of gloom
Impertinence$$the quality or state of being very rude or disrespectful
Tacit$$expressed or carried on without words or speech -- implied or indicated (as by an act or by silence) but not actually expressed
Laconic$$using or involving the use of a minimum of words -- concise to the point of seeming rude or mysterious
Vehemently$$doing something in a way marked by forceful energy, intense emotion or bitter antagonism
Amiable$$Generally agreeable -- friendly, sociable, and congenial.
Assiduous$$(adj) showing great care, attention, and effort
Taciturn$$tending to be quiet -- not speaking frequently
Corroborate$$to support with evidence or authority -- to  make more certain
Conjecture$$(N:) a conclusion deduced by guesswork -- (V:) to form an opinion or idea without proof or sufficient evidence
Accord$$(V:) to bring (something) into agreement OR to arrive at an agreement. (The newspaper does not accord with what he said; it was inaccurate)
Vociferate$$To utter / Cry out loudly
Magistrate$$a local official who has some of the powers of a judge
Culpable$$deserving blame -- guilty of doing something wrong
Equanimity$$(n:) calm emotions when dealing with problems, pressure, or great stress
Entreaties$$a plead or a serious request for something
Hector$$ to intimidate, harass, or bully by bluster or personal pressure
Ignoble$$A Pleebe. Of low birth or common origin
Consternation$$a strong feeling of surprise or sudden disappointment that causes confusion.
Affectation$$the act of taking on or displaying an attitude or mode of behavior not natural to oneself or not genuinely felt -- speech or conduct not natural to oneself
Obstinacy$$the quality or state of being obstinate
Slatternly$$untidy and dirty through habitual neglect; also :  careless, disorderly -- of, relating to, or characteristic of a slut or prostitute
Insolence$$lack of respect for rank or authority, hatred
Vapid$$lacking liveliness, tang, briskness, or force
Dilapidation$$ to turn into a condition of decay or partial ruin
Palaver$$talk that is not important or meaningful -- excitement and activity caused by something that is not important
